<TEXT>
robert penn warren who won the pulitzer 
prize three times for his novels and poetry and was named the 
nations first poet laureate has died after a threeyear battle 
with cancer 
warren 84 died early friday at his summer home his wife the 
author eleanor clark and a local doctor were with him said andrew 
king his longtime friend and strattons town clerk and treasurer 
services will be private with a public memorial service 
scheduled later said a spokesman for the covey and allen funeral 
home in wilmington 
warren was the first to win pulitzer prizes in both poetry and 
fiction the poetry prizes came in 1957 for promises poems 
19541956 and in 1979 for now and then poems 19761978 
his novel all the kings men a book about the myth 
surrounding huey long the swaggering populist governor of 
louisiana won the pulitzer in 1947 and became an academy 
awardwinning motion picture 
his other awards include the presidential medal of freedom the 
national medal for literature and the gold medal for poetry from the 
american academy and institute of arts and letters he also was 
among the first recipients of the macarthur foundations 
unrestricted genius grants 
warren was remembered as a brilliant poet fiction writer 
teacher and critic and as a nice man 
he had such vigor and such love of life he was such wonderful 
company he was the soul of hilarity said novelist and short 
story writer eudora welty whose first work was published in the 
southern review when warren was editor in the 1930s he was a good 
friend to writers constantly generous and giving 
he was reticent ironic reserved and perfectly charming and i 
loved and respected him quite apart from his work said poet 
howard nemerov who owns a copy of the first edition of warrens 
first book 
his fellow writers marveled at his versatility and virtuosity 
hes astounding said poet robert bly its very seldom 
that someone can write poetry and fiction and do it well in 
fiction you take nine or ten generations and compress them in 
poetry you take 30 seconds and expand it 
born in guthrie ky on april 24 1905 warren grew up hearing 
tales of the civil war from his two grandfathers who had been 
confederate soldiers 
warren graduated summa cum laude from vanderbilt university in 
1925 received a masters degree from the university of california 
at berkeley and studied at oxford university as a rhodes scholar 
while teaching at louisiana state university he was a founder of 
southern review from 1938 to 1961 he was an editorial adviser to 
the kenyon review 
his first fulllength novel published in 1939 was night 
rider about the plight of kentucky tobacco growers at the turn of 
the century 
other works included at heavens gate world enough and 
time band of angels wilderness a tale of the civil war 
and flood a romance for our time 
in 1986 warren was appointed poet laureate a largely ceremonial 
title created by congress 
the people who create these posts dont give a damn about 
poetry warren said of the appointment they do it because its 
a nice thing to do they think theres a poet down the road lets 
make him a poet laureate 
warren lived the last three decades of his life in new england 
before his second marriage to ms clark she had suggested that 
they return to the south so that their children would know his world 
but i discovered it wasnt the same world warren once said 
i had been carrying a dream around in my head 
</TEXT>
