an explosion saturday aboard a bus in the 
ethnically troubled republic of azerbaijan killed three people and 
injured other passengers the official tass news agency said 
in the republics capital baku the azerbaijani parliament ended 
an emergency session with a call for direct control of an enclave 
disputed with neighboring armenia the tass news agency said 
in its report on the explosion tass said the bus was traveling 
from the georgian capital of tbilisi to baku on the caspian sea 300 
miles to the southeast 
the news agency did not link the explosion to the ethnic strife 
between armenians and azerbaijanis it said the kgb secret police 
were investigating 
tass did not say how many people were injured nor did it say how 
many passengers were aboard the bus or give other details 
about 100 people have been killed in ethnic violence during the 
past 18 months in the conflict over control of the enclave of 
nagornokarabakh which is predominantly christian armenian 
the armenians want the mountainous area which is within 
azerbaijans borders to be transferred to their control 
nagornokarabakh was in mainly moslem azerbaijans jurisdiction 
until february when moscow moved in to rule the enclave directly in 
an effort to stem the violence 
the conflict has forced hundreds of thousands of armenians and 
azerbaijanis in the region to flee their homes 
tass reported the azerbaijani parliaments resolution on saturday 
claimed that nagornokarabakh is legally part of azerbaijan and 
asked moscow to reconsider its central rule over the area 
in the armenian capital of yerevan a special session of the 
republics legislature was convened to discuss the azerbaijani 
resolution the news agency also said 
communist party officials are scheduled to meet tuesday in moscow 
to consider changes in the countrys nationalities policy and seek 
ways to calm ethnic quarrels like the one between azerbaijan and 
armenia 
the azerbaijani lawmakers will soon submit for public discussion 
a proposed law to provide sovereignty of the republic or 
independent exercise of legislative executive and judicial power 
over the whole of the territory of the republic in the interests of 
its multinational population tass said 
