the agreement calls for an initial investment of 1075 million 
in the valley over the contracts sixyear exploration phase and the 
drilling of at least one exploratory well a year more than 14000 
square miles of the valley will be open for exploration 
the company is required to begin exploration work within 180 days 
mobil predicts a possible investment of 15 to 2 billion over 
the 30year extraction phase of the contract should exploration 
prove fruitful 
daniel nunez president of the stateowned petroleum company 
petroperu which represents the government in the contract said the 
area could contain as much as 1 billion barrels of oil 
